Update README.md

commit.message:
Final Commit for Release 2.0

- Maritime Trade button now disabled after placing a game piece and
the resources go to amounts where none can be utilized for trade.
- Check Release notes for details on Release 2.0.

Final Commit for Release 2.0

- Names were added to the game so that Ceten looks slightly more
realistic.
- Check the release notes for details on Release 2.0

Final touches for Release 2.0

- Code quality was slightly improved.
- Comments were made for the more elaborate algorithms utilized in
Ceten.

Fixed resource bank bug, Minor UI improvements

- Resource counts would not respect the maximum amount of resources
that the board has. The bugfix implemented fixes this.
- Roll Dice number and Tile tokens now adjust the number location more
accurately.
- Trading now properly trades resources with both the bank and the
active player (had to make relationship between player and board
bidirectional to implement this cleanly).
- Development Card UI components are now hidden since Development Cards
will not be utilized for the upcoming release.
- Victory points required to win is now 6 and the quantity of each
resources that the board starts off with is 30 to make up for the fact
that the upcoming release only contains core game mechanics.

Maritime Trade

commit.message:
Trade rates are now influenced by ports.

- Trade rate for every elements with 4:1 rate goes to 3:1 if a player
places a settlement adjacent to a standard port.
- Trade rate for a specific element goes to 2:1 if a player places
a settlement adjacent to a port specializing in that specific element.

Maritime Trading Process is complete.

- Resources are now withdrawn after the deposit phase. The amount
withdrawn depends on the amount deposited and the current trade rates.
- Feedback panel properly reflects which trading phase is active.
- UI components for maritime trading work as intended.

Added full logistics for the deposit phase of Maritime Trading

- Resources are deposited and withdrawn (to take back if the user
changes his mind) at rates based on the player's trade rate for the
resource.

Added basic logistics for Maritime Trade, Modified all Submit Buttons

- All buttons are now disabled when their usages is irrelevant to the
current phase.
- Basic logistics for Maritime Trading has been implemented (can only
submit button twice before getting out of it).

commit.message:
Mechanics of Road Placement has been completed

- When placing a settlement, it now must be next to a player's road.
- Roads cannot be placed if there is no adjacent roads from the player.
Also, a road still cannot be placed if a different player's settlement
is in the way.
- Roads are now able to be placed in a proper fashion during the
setup phase (settlements can be placed under normal conditions while
roads must be placed next to the settlement that was just placed).

Mechanics of Road Placement has been implemented.

- Spending and quantity logic works.
- Need to place roads during setup phase to verify that functionality
works (for restrictions entailing the road needing to be adjacent to
another road that belongs to the player without another player's
settlement blocking the way).

Edge Facades have been implemented

- Edges are now drawn on the UI of Ceten.
- As of now can freely be placed (no game mechanics dictating how
roads affect Ceten just yet).
- Removed unused enum for Resource Bank.

Refactoring board connections

commit.message:
Ports are now set properly, Deleted irrelevant content.

- The map builder now has new logic to determine where ports go
on the edges that connect to sea tiles (the locations of these edges
are fixed but the ports are still random).
- Deleted DevelopmentCard class (should be a new class known as
DevelopmentCardBank if development cards are implemented).
- Scrapped code that ended up being unused after some refactoring.

Existing game mechanics were modified to adapt to structural refactor.

- Mostly involving the use of corners and land tiles.
- Some code refactoring was done to improve readability.

Corner Facades are now generated

- Uses the tile facade coordinates and hex pointlist generator to
determine where the position of the corners are.
- Separated list of tile facades in board facade into a list of land
tile facades and sea tile facades (makes land tile facade exclusive
operations easier to implement).

Minor fixes implemented.

- No duplicate Tiles in Edge and Corner instances.
- Deleted methods inside Edge class (since all of them were outdated).
- Modified hex pointlist generator logic in preparation for generation
of corner facade coordinates (so the facades correspond to the right
directions within the tile).
- Removed debugging information for tile facade centers.

New algorithm to connect Tiles, Edges, and Corners implemented.

- Edges and Corners are now directly relating to Tiles, rather than
the structure being a daisy chain of Tile going to Edge, which goes
to Corner.
- Algorithm to connect all three components now involves checking
adjacent tiles of current tile and placing the contrary edge and
corners to its proper spot rather than creating new ones.

Token placement was reimplemented

- The token placement no longer relies on the now defunct relational
id to place tokens.
- An algorithm gathers all the land tiles surrounding the specified
land tile, allowing the adjacent tiles to be rejected from receiving a
6 or 8 token.

Added appropriate concrete classes for Tile Facades

- Overlooked in previous commit due to oversight.

Abstracted Tile Facade

- This allows sea tiles to not worry about user input related logic
for the robber.
- Also allows separation of concern for rendered content (e.g. no
looking through resource textures on a SeaTile).

Refactored Tile and Tile Facade

- Abstracted the Tile class since land tiles and sea tiles have
significantly different behaviour
- Tile facade has been modified so that the tile is placed based on
its hex coordinate rather than an arbitrary adjustment algorithm being
used to move each tile.
- Added new enums to dictate the hex directions for both corners
and edges.
- Corners will have to be generated based on a fixed-position array.
An adjacent tile algorithm needs to be implemented in order to
move existing corners and existing edges to new tiles. This algorithm
will also need to be used to place tokens since relational ID and
physical ID have now been scrapped.

Placed Tile Facades, Corner Facades, and Connect Board on lockdown.

- Tile facades and corner facades are the UI components that are
heavily tied to what needs to be refactored.
- Connect Board is going to be redone entirely due to the modification
of the structure between Board, Tile, Edge, and Corner.

commit.message:
Deleted remnants of pycache folder.

- Was commited before __pycache__ was put in gitignore.

Deleted irrelevant files.

- They don't do anything to contribute to the Ceten codebase itself.

New enum classes, Existing enum classes moved to separate files

- Enums were added for the current phase and current game phase to make
checked involving such variables more readable.
- Existing enums were moved to separate classes so they could be
accessed by multiple classes in a simpler manner.

Abstracted Panel Classes, Modified some functions

- Abstract panel class was made and existing panel classes inherited
that abstract class.
- Some function arguments swapped argument positions for consistency.
- Renamed some functions to more accurately reflect intended action.
